<br>
FoH just finished. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm familiar with the concept of mass recruiting Pipswich, and I'm also aware that FoH recently added a large number of new members to defeat encounters that demand that guilds be at, or close to the 72 person raid limit to defeat it. I'm also aware that those 72 people have to be the right classes.<br>
<br>
My contention is that works on some servers doesn't work on other servers.<br>
<br>
Let's start slowly.<br>
<br>
Veeshan is an old server. MT is quite a bit younger than Veeshan. <br>
<br>
Veeshan had 7 or 8 elemental guilds. MT has 3.5, soon to be 4.<br>
<br>
FoH, playing on Veeshan, could mass recruit and get the classes/numbers they needed from a pool of elemental equipped people. FE, playing on MT, has a far smaller number of elemental equipped people to recruit from. As such, FE will likely have a large number of applicants who are  underequipped relative to long term members and/or lack high end raiding experience.<br>
<br>
What are the ramifications of these differences?<br>
<br>
FoH will pretty much be able to jump right back into Time. Their alts have gear that is on par with FE members so it stands to reason that when the selected few got into FoH they would have gear that would enable to do what they couldn't do before.<br>
<br>
I don't see FE being able to do that given the difficulty of the gods in Time. I think there will be the need to go on an extended farming spree in the elemental planes to get the large number of recruits up to par in terms of hps, mana pools, focus effects, etc.<br>
<br>
That isn't an easy thing to without running the risk of alienating your long term members, particularly after the hell of learning and ultimately defeating the Rathe.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying it can't be done. I do respect the skills of long term FE members and it is entirely possible that the mass recruiting strategy will work. I'm just forced to wonder how likely that is when you have as many new applicants and members as you do (from the Rathe recruitment drive and now the Time recruitment drive).<br>
<br>
I don't think long term members of the top raiding guild on a server are loot whores by any stretch of the imagination. Rather I would say that the primary driving force is the desire to defeat the designers of the game. Generally speaking, top end guilds have a lengthy and selective recruitment process which is designed to get members who are skilled and desire a challenge. When selectivty is discarded, you tend to draw large numbers of people who are more interested in the mystique of the guild's name and the lure of loot than you would like. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dadoomz>dadoomz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/8/03 3:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1090.topic&index=46>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> COME ON, aren't we getting a little off topic? <br>
