My first statement was completely reasonable, as the non raided person simply stepped into an engagement he had no business joining, and assumed that the raid engaged wanted the help and trusted that they werent being ks'd. My point was that this person seemed to be surprised that the raid he was interfering with didnt aid him (by healing him). It is no surprise at all that they didnt heal him, as he had no business even engaging that mob, unless and until he was asked to help. To assume that a raid needs or wants help simply because their MA died is unreasonable, as many raids are successful even if the MA dies. Or are we to now accept that anyone can make such a call, as to whether a raid is about to wipe, and proceed to enter that engagement?<br>
  My second statement was in response to Fogel assuming I was being sarcastic, which I wasnt. I was pointing out that if you decide to engage a mob that is already engaged by others, it really isnt reasonable to expect them to assist you, considering they didnt ask for, and perhaps didnt need your help. My original statement stands, this person had no business engaging a mob that was already engaged.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twompypyrognomiac>Twompy Pyrognomiac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/9/03 12:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1090.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thanks to the person in AV or MLF that dispelled</span><hr size=1> You certainly have every right to not want outside help, I usually tend to think the same way. And you were certainly not obligated to heal the melee that added your fight. But to be worried about a tank ksing, or pulling the mob away from you at that point in the fight (even if he did get agro he'd be summoned if he tried to run) is pretty paranoid. <br>
